<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-13 01:20:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Chamberlain Told All in Interview </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Of course, Bill Russell was a prime topic in  
one of the final interviews of Wilt Chamberlain's life. So were all 
the details of his many losses to the Boston Celtics. 
</P>
<P>
	``Don't ask me how I remember them,'' Chamberlain said. ``I've  
never forgotten them, you understand?'' 
</P>
<P>
	Chamberlain, who rarely did interviews in recent years, sat down  
for a television piece produced by the Philadelphia 76ers in May. 
Portions of the three-hour interview, conducted by longtime Philly 
sports anchor Al Meltzer, aired this summer on local cable. 
</P>
<P>
	It was a revealing talk in which Chamberlain spoke of regrets,  
his history with women and the man he thought was the best 
basketball player of all time. 
</P>
<P>
	Believe it or not, it was Meadowlark Lemon.  
</P>
<P>
	``Meadowlark was the most sensational, awesome, incredible  
basketball player I've ever seen,'' Chamberlain said. ``People 
would say it would be Dr. J or even Michael Jordan. For me it would 
be Meadowlark Lemon.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Chamberlain's bravado really came through. He bragged about  
wanting to fight Muhammad Ali, explained why he publicized the 
number of women he'd slept with and lamented his teams' many 
failures against Russell's Boston Celtics. 
</P>
<P>
	``I guarantee you, if you could give me 10 points in all those  
seventh games against the Boston Celtics, instead of Bill Russell 
having 11 rings, I could've at least had nine or eight,'' 
Chamberlain said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Bill Russell -- very, very proud man. He thought his game of  
basketball was as good as anybody who ever played the game. He 
might not tell you that, but that's how he feels. And he may be 
right. With the rings, he can prove that he's right to some 
degree.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Chamberlain, who died Tuesday in Los Angeles, also expressed  
mixed feelings about Jordan. 
</P>
<P>
	``If (John) Paxson hadn't made that 3-point shot for Chicago  
five or six years ago, that would be one less championship for 
Jordan,'' Chamberlain said. ``If (Steve) Kerr hadn't made the 
3-point shot, that's one more less championship for Jordan. Does 
that make Jordan a different guy, a different player? Does that 
make him any less great than he is because he lost two or three 
games? 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm saying this because you ask me: My disappointment is that  
some people view me as a loser. They hold up other guys as winners 
because they won the gold ring and I didn't.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Chamberlain won two championships, with the 76ers in 1967 and  
Los Angeles Lakers in 1972. 
</P>
<P>
	He said he was close to signing a contract to fight Ali while  
Chamberlain was still playing basketball, and that renowned trainer 
Cus D'Amato wanted to train him for the fight. 
</P>
<P>
	The fight never happened because of money, Chamberlain said.  
</P>
<P>
	His on-and-off appearances with the Harlem Globetrotters scared  
him, ``because I liked them so well that I did not want to come 
back and play in the NBA.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``You must understand as a kid of color in those days, the  
Harlem Globetrotters were like being movie stars,'' Chamberlain 
said. ``You know, this was your dream.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Criticized for claiming in his autobiography that he'd slept  
with 20,000 women, Chamberlain explained why he did so. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're all fascinated by the numbers, as we were about the 100  
points,'' Chamberlain said. ``... So I thought of a number that was 
a round number that may be close and may be whatever, and I used 
that number. Now according to the average person, that number is so 
preposterous that I can understand them not believing it. 
</P>
<P>
	``But the point of using the number was to show that sex was a  
great part of my life as basketball was a great part of my life. 
That's the reason why I was single.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Chamberlain said he regretted not explaining the sexual climate  
at the time of his escapades. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a different sexual situation going on than it is in the  
'80s and '90s, and I did a very poor job of describing that,'' said 
Chamberlain, who offered a warning for any men who admired him for 
it. 
</P>
<P>
	``With all of you men out there who think that having a thousand  
different ladies is pretty cool, I have learned in my life. I've 
found out that having one woman a thousand different times is much 
more satisfying.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
