<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Giants Hire Thompson, Righetti </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- The San Francisco Giants replaced their  
first base and pitching coaches on Wednesday, with former All-Star 
players Robby Thompson and Dave Righetti joining the staff. 
</P>
<P>
	Thompson takes over from Carlos Alfonso as first base coach and  
Righetti replaces Ron Perranoski as pitching coach. Alfonso will be 
the team's administrative coach and video coordinator next season 
and Perranoski has been appointed special assistant to the general 
manager. 
</P>
<P>
	Thompson and Righetti were teammates on the Giants' 1993 team  
and both served as roving minor league instructors this past 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Thompson, 37, retired as an active player in 1997. He was San  
Francisco's No. 1 draft pick in 1983 and was named 1986 National 
League Rookie of the Year. He holds a number of team records for 
second basemen, including career games (1,304), at-bats (4,612), 
home runs (119) and stolen bases (103). 
</P>
<P>
	Righetti, 40, was named American League Rookie of the Year in  
1981 and was All-Star in 1986-87 with the Yankees. He threw a 
no-hitter against the Boston Red Sox on July 4, 1983 at Yankee 
Stadium. In his 16-year career, he played for the Yankees, Giants, 
Oakland, Toronto, and the Chicago White Sox. He established a Major 
League record with 46 saves in 1986. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
