<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Cancer Testing Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- In a story Oct. 5 on colon cancer testing, The  
Associated Press erroneously stated the guideline of the American 
College of Physicians for persons who test positive in a fecal 
occult blood test. 
</P>
<P>
	The guideline states that a person testing positive should be  
followed up with either a complete colonoscopy, or with a flexible 
sigmoidoscopy plus an air-contrast barium enema X-ray exam. 
</P>
<P>
	The story erroneously implied that the barium enema is  
recommended with both of the other procedures. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
