<HEADLINE> Morris Signing at Reagan Library </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SIMI VALLEY, Calif. (AP) -- Edmund Morris signed copies of his  
new Ronald Reagan biography at Reagan's presidential library, 
saying his subject was never a ``bookish, nerdy intellectual like 
myself.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Morris told about 40 people at the library Tuesday that the more  
time he spent with Reagan ``the more astonished I was by his 
private ordinariness and his public majesty.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Morris has been attacked for injecting fictional elements into  
``Dutch: A Memoir of Ronald Reagan.'' He thanked the library for 
allowing him to appear, citing the ``potential embarrassment.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Whatever embarrassment Mr. Morris feels is his own,'' said  
Mark Burson, executive director of the library. ``We aren't 
embarrassed to have him here.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The library did not send out the usual press notices that Morris  
would appear. 
  	   	
