<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pregnant Girl's Dad Defends Church </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The father of a 12-year-old who is getting  
financial help from the Roman Catholic Church to dissuade her from 
having an abortion has denied that she is being bribed. 
</P>
<P>
	In an interview published today, he also said the 15-year-old  
boy who made her pregnant should be prosecuted. 
</P>
<P>
	The father, whose name was not revealed, was quoted as telling  
London's Daily Mail that his daughter has severe learning 
difficulties and a reading age of six, but was adamant about 
keeping the baby. 
</P>
<P>
	``Both my wife and I are very distressed that people think she  
is being bribed to keep her child, which couldn't be further from 
the truth,'' the 35-year-old father, who is Catholic, was quoted as 
saying. ``We vowed to support her whatever decision she came to.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The case has focused attention on a controversial program called  
Pro-Life Initiative. Under the program, Scotland's staunchly 
conservative Cardinal Thomas Winning gives money and other help to 
encourage women not to have abortions. The girls' parents 
approached the program for help. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement that the Catholic Church was paying the family  
provoked a furious backlash Monday from abortion rights advocates, 
who said it was tantamount to bribery. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl lives in Torbay, in the southwest England county of  
Devon, with her parents. Both the parents are on welfare, and they 
have two other children. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl's parents plan to raise the baby, due early next year,  
the father said. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl and the 15-year-old boy who impregnated her were pupils  
at a special school. 
</P>
<P>
	``He should be made an example of. My daughter is 12 years old,  
for God's sake,'' the father was quoted as saying. ``I went down to 
see the boy and his parents, but they don't want to know. His 
mother's exact words were, 'Oh Christ, I've got 18 grandchildren 
already.' It is utterly irresponsible.'' 
</P>
<P>
	It is illegal to have sex with a girl under 16, but Devon police  
said no complaint had been made. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl is the third 12-year-old who has attracted publicity  
here recently for either having a baby or becoming pregnant. 
Britain has Western Europe's highest teen pregnancy rate, and Prime 
Minister Tony Blair has declared a moral crusade to counter the 
problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
