<HEADLINE> Warrener, Sabres in Two-Year Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Rhett Warrener has agreed to a two-year  
contract with the Buffalo Sabres worth about $1.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The Sabres acquired the 23-year-old defenseman in a trade with  
Florida last March. He was the final restricted free agent to come 
to terms with the team. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a little bit of a relief,'' general manager Darcy Regier  
said. ``It's nice to have it behind us because it allows us to 
focus on the groups of guys that were here at the end of last 
year.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Sabres have yet to reach an agreement with unrestricted free  
agent Joe Juneau. 
  	   	
</P>
