<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 52-Week T-Bills Interest Rates Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The interest rate on 52-week Treasury bills  
rose in Wednesday's auction to the highest level in nearly 16 
months. 
</P>
<P>
	The discount rate was 5.115 percent, up from 5.000 percent at  
the last auction on Sept. 14. It was the highest rate since 52-week 
bills sold for 5.130 percent on June 18, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	The bills will carry an equivalent coupon interest rate of 5.411  
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,482.80. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales totaled $10 billion out of bids of $23.5 billion.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
