<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Schwab Issues $10M Challenge Grant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHAPEL HILL, N.C. (AP) -- A foundation set up by financier  
Charles R. Schwab has made a $10 million matching challenge to a 
group that helps learning disabled students. 
</P>
<P>
	The gift to All Kinds of Minds, a non-profit organization  
affiliated with the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, 
requires the group to raise $20 million over five years. A prorated 
amount will be given if less is raised by the program. 
</P>
<P>
	The Schwab Foundation for Learning was formed by Charles and  
Helen O'Neill Schwab after their son was diagnosed with dyslexia in 
the late 1980s. Schwab also recognized he had a similar, 
undiagnosed condition in his youth. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
