<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-13 14:50:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Raptors Coach in E-Mail Flap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Butch Carter, coach of the NBA Toronto  
Raptors, wants his ex-wife to keep out of his personal e-mail 
messages. 
</P>
<P>
	Lawyers for Carter said in court that his ex-wife, Jill Carter,  
is reading and then distributing her ex-husband's e-mail messages 
from an account he has with LoveAOL, an America Online personal 
advertising service. She and his lawyers are at odds over whether 
she has a right to see his e-mail. 
</P>
<P>
	Judge Ann Marie Tracey granted Carter a temporary order Tuesday  
in Hamilton County Common Pleas Court. The order forbids Jill 
Carter to distribute the e-mails for at least 14 days. 
</P>
<P>
	The coach's lawyers asked for the order to prevent Carter's  
ex-wife from gaining access to his e-mail account, reading it, 
printing the messages, disseminating them or contacting those who 
sent him e-mail. 
</P>
<P>
	Carter loaned his laptop computer to a son who was going to  
Mexico and wanted to check his e-mail. When the son returned home 
in July, Jill Carter somehow learned her ex-husband's AOL password 
and gained access to his LoveAOL account, the coach's lawyers said. 
</P>
<P>
	Carter's lawyers suggested that his ex-wife was being vindictive  
and using the e-mails to embarrass and harass Carter and those with 
whom he exchanges e-mail. 
</P>
<P>
	Phyllis Bossin, Jill Carter's lawyer, did not return a telephone  
call to her office Wednesday for comment. 
</P>
<P>
	The Carters were married from 1981 to 1988 and had three sons --  
now ages 17, 14 and 8 -- before divorcing. They then lived together 
in the mid-1990s when Carter was an assistant with the Milwaukee 
Bucks. 
</P>
<P>
	Jill Carter lives in Cincinnati. Butch Carter, a former high  
school basketball star in Middletown, Ohio, now lives in Toronto. 
He has been the Raptors' coach since February 1998. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
