<HEADLINE>  Packers Fans Stake Claims to Turf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- They came to Lambeau Field in pickup  
trucks, bearing scythes, hacksaws, machetes, even steak knives. 
</P>
<P>
	Green Bay Packers fans weren't staging a coup. They came to  
carve a chunk of Lambeau Field history. 
</P>
<P>
	Fans descended on the field's parking lot Tuesday and Wednesday  
to take home pieces of the high-tech, low-effectiveness SportGrass 
