<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Wednesday, Oct. 13, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Stocks End Lower; Dow Down 184.90  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks fell steeply for a second straight  
session as Intel's disappointing earnings report hammered 
technology shares and plunging bond prices dragged the broader 
market lower. At the close of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones 
industrial average was down 184.90 at 10,232.16, extending its drop 
of 231.12 yesterday. Broader stock indicators were also sharply 
lower. The Nasdaq composite index fell 70.97 to 2,801.46. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures just before 3 p.m. EDT:  
Dow Industrials:        10,232.16  - 184.90
NYSE Issues:         Advances  907  Declines 2,150  Unchgd  472
