<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NFL Tells Titans They Were Right </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- The Tennessee Titans have learned that  
one problem with instant replay can be playing in a regional game 
where only two camera angles are available to officials. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Jeff Fisher said Wednesday that the NFL informed him he  
was correct in challenging a catch by Baltimore's Patrick Johnson 
Sunday in the Titans' 14-11 victory over Baltimore. The catch for 
14 yards came on third-and-8 and kept a drive alive for a field 
goal in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Referee Dick Hantak only got two views, the second coming 80  
seconds into the review. Both were inconclusive, so Hantak upheld 
the ruling of a completed pass. Fisher said another view in New 
York clearly showed that Johnson failed to hold onto the ball. 
</P>
<P>
	``Some teams are going have many more feeds in some games than  
other teams based on the national TV and the number of cameras,'' 
Fisher said. ``I almost have to take that into consideration when 
we challenge.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
